%rebase('base.tpl', title='Privacy Policy')

<div>
    <hgroup>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Version: 0.0.1 updated 07.03.2025</p>
    </hgroup>

    <section>
        <h3>About this app</h3>
        <p>This Privacy Policy applies to the "TinyDB on GCS Form" application (the "App"), which is designed to test
            the functioning of a new database engine. The App is a proof-of-concept (POC) and will store data on Google
            Cloud Platform (GCP).</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Information Collection</h3>
        <p>The App collects the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>user input: mail, name, message</li>
            <li>system logs</li>
            <li>* No personally identifiable information other then Mail & IP (PII) will be collected or stored.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Data Storage</h3>
        <p>All data collected by the App will be stored on Google Cloud Platform (GCP) servers. GCP's privacy and
            security policies can be found at [https://cloud.google.com/security](https://cloud.google.com/security).
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Data Retention</h3>
        <p>Data collected by the App will be retained for the duration of the POC, which is expected to be 3 months.
            After the POC is completed, all data will be deleted.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Data Sharing</h3>
        <p>No data collected by the App will be shared with third parties, except as required by law or to comply with a
            court order.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Security</h3>
        <p>The App uses industry-standard security measures to protect data, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>encryption at rest</li>
            <li>encryption in transite</li>
            <li>Access Control to storage & keys</li>
            <li>Static scans</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Contact Us</h3>
        <p>
            If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at admin@hermanowicz.co
            By using the App, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to this Privacy Policy.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
